title: Net interest margin of banks in the U.S. 1995 to 2019
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Net interest margin. In total the number of data points it has is 25.
In general Net interest margin has fallen over the Year.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2009 and 2010.
Maximum Net interest margin, about 4.3 was reported at Year 1996, and 1997
The lowest Net interest margin, of value 2.98 was reported at Year 2015
